- Sun 25 Nov 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=97a997e756

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 24 Nov 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 412, 365 confirmed and 47 probable. In total, there were 236 deaths (189 confirmed and 47 probable) and 120 people healed.
- 75 suspected cases under investigation.
- 9 new confirmed cases, including 4 in Beni, 2 in Butembo, 2 in Kalunguta, and 1 in Katwa [all in North Kivu].
- 5 new confirmed case deaths, including 2 in Beni, 2 in Butembo, and 1 in Katwa.

News of the response
Community involvement
---------------------
- This Sat 24 Nov 2018, an awareness activity was organized in Butembo for all transport agencies in the city. Awareness focused on Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) in general, prevention methods, and the importance of respecting washing and temperature control points installed along the roads.
- The program of projection of educational films on EVD was launched in Beni, Kanzulinzuli district in Ndindi, this Sat 24 Nov 2018. About 280 people living in the neighborhood attended the screening which will also be organized in 10 other neighborhoods of the city.

Vaccination
-----------
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 35 389 people have been vaccinated, including 16 997 in Beni [the total numbers of people vaccinated in North Kivu and Ituri provinces can be seen at the source URL above].
- Of those vaccinated, 10 110 are front-line providers.

