Uganda wants to be ready if #Ebola shows up in health centers near its border with DRC. This is the 1st time an Ebola vaccine has been used to prepare in this way.

Helen Branswell added,
https://twitter.com/WHOUganda/status/1066754846685102081
WHO Uganda
#EbolaVaccination update: Vaccination going on well. As of 25 Nov 2018, 1175 health workers in the 3 districts of Kasese, Ntoroko & Bundibugyo have been vaccinated. On Tue 27 Nov 2018, the vaccination team will move to the 4th district (Kabarole). #Uganda

WHO Uganda@WHOUganda
As a result of the #EbolaVaccination. the various teams of health-workers in the field are more encouraged, feel appreciated and cared for, and are willing to give their all to prevent and/or STOP this epidemic from occurring or spreading into #Uganda.

